{"id":"0907.3745","submitter":"Molaro Paolo","authors":"Pierluigi Selvelli, Paolo Molaro","title":"On the telescopes in the paintings of J. Brueghel the Elder","comments":"5 pages, 3 figures. Proceedings of 400 years of Astronomical\n  telescopes Conference at ESA/ESTEC in Noordwijk. Brandl, Bernhard R.; Stuik,\n  Remko; Katgert-Merkeli, J.K. (Jet) (Eds.)","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph.IM","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We have investigated the nature and the origin of the telescopes depicted in\nthree paintings of J. Bruegel the Elder completed between 1609 and 1618. The\n\"tube\" that appears in the painting dated 1608-1612 represents a very early\ndutch spyglass, tentatively attributable to Sacharias Janssen or Lipperhey,\nprior to those made by Galileo, while the two instruments made of several\ndraw-tubes which appear in the two paintings of 1617 and 1618 are quite\nsophisticated and may represent early examples of Keplerian telescopes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2009 15:38:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-07-23"}
